    "Such work has given rise to what can be called forward stress testing (FST), where analysts impose an assumed shock and observe its consequences.",
    "Even though FST has attracted interest of the regulatory industry and academia as a promising approach for evaluating risk and resilience in supply chains 5, its strength is also its weakness.",
    "Every forward stress test depends on the choice of initiating threat events.",
    "In global supply chains, the number of possible disruptions is effectively limitless, ranging from natural disasters and labor strikes to geopolitical conflict and data failures.",
